1968;;The Private Navy of Sgt. O'Farrell;;American;;Frank Tashlin;;Bob Hope, Jeffrey Hunter, Phyllis Diller;;war comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Private_Navy_of_Sgt._O%27Farrell;;Master Sergeant Dan O'Farrell is a G.I. on an island somewhere in the South Pacific during World War II, bemoaning the loss of a ship torpedoed while ferrying to the island a desperately needed cargo of beer.<br><br>Among his problems are the Navy personnel making life difficult for him and his Army buddies, an officer trying to emulate John Paul Jones, a hoped-for delivery of morale-boosting nurses turning out to be six men, the ugliest woman (Diller) ever to wilt a bouquet of flowers, and a Japanese soldier who has been hiding from everyone else and hiding something else as well.